goals.question: What is the distribution of airport names by first letter?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of first letter of name field
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the distribution of airport names by first letter and identify any patterns or outliers.

code:

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='name_length', color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['name_length'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['name_length'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['name_length'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['name_length'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names by length?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.countplot(x="country", data=data, order = data['country'].value_counts().index)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    chart.set(xlabel='Country', ylabel='Number of Airports')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    data['first_letter'] = data['name'].str[0]
    data = data.groupby('first_letter').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    ax = sns.barplot(x='first_letter', y='counts', data=data, color='b')
    ax.axhline(y=data['counts'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    plt.xlabel('First Letter of Airport Name')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names by first letter?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
